{"id":79499,"title":"Steroids vs immunotherapy for allergic rhinitis - out with the old, in with the new.","abstract":"Treatment for seasonal allergic rhinitis induced by airborne allergens can be divided into two major groups: symptom-dampening drugs, such as antihistamines and corticosteroids, and disease-modifying drugs in the form of immunotherapy. It has been speculated that depot-injection corticosteroids given once or twice a year are a safe and patient-friendly alternative to the time-consuming immunotherapy. Our data indicate otherwise. ","date":"2014-01-13","categories":"Otorhinolaryngologic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24410534","annotations":[{"name":"Rhinitis","weight":0.849915,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rhinitis"},{"name":"Allergic rhinitis","weight":0.844161,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allergic_rhinitis"},{"name":"Immunotherapy","weight":0.801314,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunotherapy"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.798817,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Histamine antagonist","weight":0.78464,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histamine_antagonist"},{"name":"Allergy","weight":0.723286,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allergy"},{"name":"Corticosteroid","weight":0.711964,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corticosteroid"},{"name":"Steroid","weight":0.687846,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steroid"},{"name":"Allergen","weight":0.579861,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allergen"},{"name":"Airborne forces","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airborne_forces"},{"name":"Alternative rock","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alternative_rock"},{"name":"Season","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Season"},{"name":"Data","weight":0.0147415,"wikiped